The paper deals with moving object detection, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of robust principal component analysis (RPCA) and group sparsity constrained nuclear norm minimization suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of segmentation techniques and the evaluation of results on video datasets suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT).
